---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Compress PDF Online — Free PDF Compressor & Image Compressor | Compressly"
  description="Compress PDF and images online for free. Learn how to compress a PDF or compress images (JPG, PNG, WEBP) with our fast, private, in-browser tool."
  canonical="/"
  ogImage="/og-image.png"
  keywords="Compress pdf, compress pdf file, compress image, compress jpg, how to compress a pdf, how to compress pdf files, compress"
>

<!-- ── HERO ── -->
<section class="hero-section" style="padding: 80px 0 64px;">
  <div class="hero-gradient"></div>
  <div class="container" style="position:relative; z-index:1; text-align:center;">
    <p class="mono-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Free · No signup · Runs in browser</p>
    <h1 class="display-xl" style="margin-bottom:16px; max-width:680px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
      Compress Images Instantly
    </h1>
    <p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--body); max-width:480px; margin:0 auto 32px;">
      Shrink JPG, PNG, and WEBP files without killing quality. Drag, drop, done.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="#compress-tool" class="btn-primary" style="font-size:15px; padding:10px 22px;">
        Start Compressing ↓
      </a>
      <a href="/pdf-compress" class="btn-secondary" style="font-size:15px; padding:10px 22px;">
        PDF Compress →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── AD BANNER TOP ── -->
<div class="container" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
  <!-- Google AdSense: replace data-ad-client and data-ad-slot -->
  <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-banner" id="ad-top">
    <span>Advertisement · AdSense banner will show here</span>
  </div>
  <!-- Uncomment after AdSense approval:
  <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-slot="XXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
  <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
  -->
</div>

<!-- ── MAIN TOOL ── -->
<section id="compress-tool" class="section-sm">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 300px; gap:32px; align-items:start;" class="tool-grid">

      <!-- LEFT: Tool -->
      <div>
        <!-- Upload Zone -->
        <div class="upload-zone" id="uploadZone">
          <input type="file" id="fileInput" accept="image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp" multiple />
          <div id="uploadPrompt">
            <div style="font-size:48px; margin-bottom:12px;">🖼️</div>
            <p class="heading-md" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Drop images here</p>
            <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--mute); margin-bottom:16px;">JPG, PNG, WEBP supported · Multiple files OK</p>
            <button type="button" class="btn-primary" onclick="document.getElementById('fileInput').click()">
              Choose Files
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Quality Slider -->
        <div class="feature-card" style="margin-top:16px;" id="settingsPanel" hidden>
          <div class="slider-wrap">
            <label>
              <span>Compression Quality</span>
              <span id="qualityValue" style="font-family:var(--font-mono); color:var(--link);">75%</span>
            </label>
            <input type="range" id="qualitySlider" min="10" max="100" value="75" />
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between;" class="body-sm" style="color:var(--mute);">
              <span style="color:var(--mute); font-size:12px;">Smaller file</span>
              <span style="color:var(--mute); font-size:12px;">Better quality</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top:16px; display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; align-items:center;">
            <button class="btn-primary" id="compressBtn">⚡ Compress All</button>
            <button class="btn-secondary" id="clearBtn">✕ Clear</button>
            <span class="body-sm" style="color:var(--mute); margin-left:auto;" id="fileCount"></span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Results List -->
        <div id="resultsList" style="margin-top:16px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px;"></div>

        <!-- Download All button -->
        <div id="downloadAllWrap" hidden style="margin-top:16px;">
          <button class="btn-primary" id="downloadAllBtn" style="width:100%; justify-content:center; padding:12px;">
            ⬇️ Download All Compressed
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RIGHT: Sidebar Ad + Info -->
      <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:16px;">
        <!-- Sidebar Ad -->
        <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-sidebar" id="ad-sidebar">
          <span>Advertisement<br/>Sidebar ad</span>
        </div>
        <!-- Info card -->
        <div class="feature-card">
          <p class="mono-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:12px;">How it works</p>
          <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:10px;" class="body-md">
            <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:flex-start;">
              <span>1️⃣</span><span>Upload JPG, PNG, or WEBP images</span>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:flex-start;">
              <span>2️⃣</span><span>Adjust quality slider (75% is sweet spot)</span>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:flex-start;">
              <span>3️⃣</span><span>Click Compress & download</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Features -->
        <div class="feature-card">
          <p class="mono-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:12px;">Features</p>
          <ul style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px; list-style:none;" class="body-md">
            <li>✅ Runs 100% in browser</li>
            <li>✅ No file size limit</li>
            <li>✅ Files never uploaded</li>
            <li>✅ JPG · PNG · WEBP</li>
            <li>✅ Batch compress</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<!-- ── SEO CONTENT: 600-word keyword-optimized description for homepage ── -->
<section id="seo-content" class="section" aria-label="About Compressly - Compress PDF and Images">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:880px;">
    <h2 class="heading-lg" style="margin-bottom:20px; text-align:left;">Compress PDF, Images, and Save Space — Fast & Private</h2>
    <p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--body); text-align:left;">
      Compress pdf files quickly and securely with Compressly — a free, browser-based tool built for speed, privacy, and simplicity. If you're searching for how to compress a pdf or how to compress pdf files without losing quality, Compressly gives you an easy, no-friction solution. Our tool lets you compress pdf, compress jpg, and optimize web images (PNG, WEBP) right in your browser so your files never leave your device.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Many people need to compress pdf file attachments for email, reduce upload times, or shrink archival documents. Compressly focuses on smart compression that balances file size and visual quality. Choose a target quality, preview results, and download instantly. Whether you need to compress pdf for work, school, or sharing photos, our interface makes it simple to compress image files and PDF documents with a single click.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Why use Compressly? First, it runs entirely in your web browser — that means privacy by design: we never upload your files to any server. Second, it supports the formats you use most: JPG, PNG, WEBP, and PDF. Third, compressing is fast because all processing happens locally. If you want to compress jpg or convert a high-resolution PNG into a smaller web-friendly image, select your files, pick a quality, and compress. For PDFs, Compressly compresses embedded images inside PDFs, which often yields significant savings while preserving text and layout.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Best practices: when you compress pdf files for email, aim for 60–80% quality for general use, and 40–60% for heavy compression where file size matters more than print-quality fidelity. If you need to compress pdf for archiving, keep a slightly higher quality. When compressing images, test a few quality settings to find the sweet spot where visual differences are minimal but file size drops substantially.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Compressly is free to use and requires no account. The tool is perfect for users who want to compress pdf files quickly, compress image files before uploading to websites, or reduce storage costs. Because the work is done locally, it also works offline and in constrained environments.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Common tasks our users complete: compress pdf before emailing, compress jpg for web galleries, compress image assets for faster page load times, and batch-compress multiple files at once. If you're wondering how to compress a pdf on desktop or in-browser, Compressly provides a consistent experience across devices without complicated installs.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      Get started now: drag and drop a PDF or image onto the tool, choose a quality setting, and click Compress. Preview the before/after file sizes and download your optimized file. Compressly helps you compress pdf and images quickly so you can share, upload, and store files more efficiently.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px;">
      We care about transparency and user control. Compression settings are visible and reversible — you decide the balance between size and quality. For most users, compressing a pdf or a jpg yields 50–80% smaller files with almost invisible quality loss. Try different settings to find what works best for your needs.
    </p>
    <p class="body-md" style="color:var(--body); margin-top:14px; margin-bottom:8px;">
      Ready to reduce file size and speed up sharing? Use Compressly to compress pdf, compress jpg, and optimize images — free, fast, and private. If you have questions about how to compress pdf files or which quality setting to choose, check our FAQ above or reach out via the About page.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── SEO FAQ Section (visible) + JSON-LD for FAQPage ── -->
<!-- Site pages links (visible on homepage) -->
<section class="section-sm">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:880px; display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <a href="/about" class="btn-secondary">About</a>
    <a href="/privacy" class="btn-secondary">Privacy Policy</a>
    <a href="/terms" class="btn-secondary">Terms & Conditions</a>
